page.title: 01Willingham, Cambridgeshire
page.content: {Willingham, a Fenland Village.} This block includes most of the village of{Willingham}and an area between the village and the{River {Great Ouse.}The area is mainly agricultural land with some fruit orchards and market gardening. It is low lying fen land, the highest point being no more than 6 metres above sea level. The village of Willingham with a population of approximately 2700, is situated about 10 miles north of the university city of{Cambridge.}It is well served by the main road network, being near the end of the M11 motorway and within a few miles of the A1 trunk road. The remains of an{Iron Age fort can be seen at Belsar's Hill. The village has expanded rapidly in recent years, many of the residents working in Cambridge.
